PBS
```json
{
  "application": "PBS",
  "description": "This script is a PBS submission wrapper for the blahpd server. It takes a command as input and sets up a PBS job with appropriate options based on the provided arguments.",
  "requirements": [
    "PBS or Torque batch system",
    "Bash shell",
    "blah_common_submit_functions.sh script",
    "qsub and qdel commands",
    "date command",
    "grep command",
    "awk command",
    "sleep command",
    "find command",
    "hostname command",
    "blah_job_registry_add script (optional)"
  ],
  "options": [
    "-c <command>",
    "-i <stdin>",
    "-o <stdout>",
    "-e <stderr>",
    "-w working dir",
    "-q <queue>",
    "-g <gianduiotto>",
    "-n <MPI nodes>",
    "-r <proxy renew time>",
    "-p <proxy path>",
    "-l <proxy lifetime>"
  ]
}
```
